Hello,

I am not certain what JVC spec mandates regarding compounded if statements 
but in MS J++ 6.0 this will fail if threshold is null. I do realize that this 
may be a valid code, but it could be made more compartible across JVMs.

  public
  boolean isAsSevereAsThreshold(Priority priority) {
    return ((threshold == null) || priority.isGreaterOrEqual(threshold));
  }
